Faxonius is a genus of malacostracans in the family Cambaridae. There are more than 20 described species in Faxonius. It includes the rusty crayfish an invasive species in North America, and three species, F. virilis,F. immunis and F. limosus that are invasive species in Europe.
Several former Orconectes species were added in 2017, leaving only the cave dwelling species unchanged.